Here's a list of 50 basic Linux commands:

pwd - Print working directory
ls - List files and directories
cd - Change directory
cp - Copy files or directories
mv - Move or rename files or directories
rm - Remove files or directories
mkdir - Create a new directory
rmdir - Remove an empty directory
touch - Create an empty file
cat - Concatenate and display the content of files
less - Display content of files page by page
head - Display the first lines of a file
tail - Display the last lines of a file
nano - A simple text editor
vim - A powerful text editor
chmod - Change file permissions
chown - Change file owner and group
chgrp - Change group ownership of a file
ps - Display information about running processes
top - Display real-time system statistics
kill - Terminate a process
killall - Kill processes by name
man - Display the manual for a command
cpufreq-info - Display CPU frequency information
df - Display disk space usage
du - Display file and directory space usage
free - Display amount of free and used memory
df - Display disk space usage
du - Display file and directory space usage
free - Display amount of free and used memory
grep - Search for a pattern in files
find - Search for files and directories
tar - Create or extract compressed archive files
gzip - Compress or decompress files
gunzip - Decompress files
ping - Check network connectivity
ifconfig - Display or configure network interfaces
route - Display or configure routing table
ssh - Connect to a remote server
scp - Copy files between local and remote machines
wget - Download files from the internet
curl - Transfer data with URLs
history - Display command history
alias - Create or display command aliases
date - Display or set the system date and time
cal - Display a calendar
who - Display information about logged-in users
passwd - Change user password
sudo - Execute a command as a superuser
shutdown - Shut down the system
